caption: Only giving a one star because the food was bomb. HOWEVER the owner Eric told me and my boyfriend that we either had to pay for a new hookah or leave because we didn’t like the flavor. Sooo we left and will not be returning. I felt completely disrespected and definitely not recommending this place to ANYONE.
Cool atmosphere and tasty Sangria 🍷

Nice sophisticated bar. The spinach artichoke Flatbread was very good. The crust was soft yet crisp at the same time. Fresh veggies 😋 The appetizer chicken wings were lightly sauced, which I prefer, but other guests at the table thought they lacked sauce. The waitress were prompt and helpful with menu selections. The indoor/outdoor seating options were very nice as well. I would recommend visiting this hip location.

I never write bad reviews. If I have a bad experience, I keep it to myself and move on. This place is on another level. My boyfriend and I walked in on a Wednesday night and the place was empty save 2-3 other people. I asked the bartender for a menu and he proceeded to treat me like a child and spoke to me in the most condescending tone. The sangria I had was the worst I've ever had ("tropical paradise" - apparently rum, cheap white wine, a cherry and a bit of diced pineapple). My boyfriend's Old fashioned was admittedly better. Art and ambience is fine. I was so put off by how the bartender treated me - and only me, as he was fine with the other customers, that I could not eat there. We had one drink each and left. I was extremely disappointed and it seems poor customer service is a running theme here. I will not be back.
Great atmosphere but i think that they should a better drink selection. Our sangrias tasted horrible. Customer service could have been better too.
Great service
Nice late night spot. Pool table. Close to out hotel and nice way to wind down night from Ybor.
Went here on super bowl weekend and the guy at the door let multiple people in yet keep telling my friends and I that they were at capacity. The man was very rude and disrespectful.
Great peeps and ambiance! Jocelyn, the bartender is awesome and hot 🔥!

(Translated by Google) Excellent atmosphere but the cocktails are juices with very little alcohol, good service and elegant place.  (Original) Excelente ambiente pero los cócteles son jugos con muy poco alcohol, buen servicio y elegante lugar.
Great taste! Ask for the sauce on the meatballs to be hot.
Love this place! Eric is an awesome bartender!! Drinks are delicious!! Will for sure be back soon!

The sangrias here are amazing!!! They have two sizes glass or a bucket. Definitely go for the bucket! It's only a few dollars more and well worth it. I went here late night with one of my friends after leaving another place. The hookahs here are also awesome and the bartenders are super nice and sweet. I haven't had a chance to try their food yet but my friend had the wings and said they were to die for. Definitely a nice go to spot for food, hookah, drinks and good vibes.

Nice location/ decent concept but you need to consider what you’re getting for your money. Very small size sangria with ice is $10 but you can get table side great sangria at Columbia cafe next door for $8. I think if you all tweak a few things such as value for what you get for your $ then you will do better and draw a better crowd. Also maybe do some more weekly  specials and events might help. Just some constructive criticism.  Update: great Sunday funday bottomless drinks and drag show! Great addition to neighborhood

Really laid back atmosphere with good sandgria but customer service is horrible. I hade issues with my truck getting towed in the parking lot in the back ($240) so the next time I came back I spoke with the manager on duty and asked if he could warn coustmers and he brushed me off. He told me that I can't speak to everyone that comes in here, so I just dropped it that was not what I was saying but there are things that you can do that dose not require you to speak with everyone that enteres. Like something on the door or have bartenders/servers bring up in conversation but also I have seen people not happy with food or drink and they do not care the response is I can give you a togo box or a togo cup that's the best I can do if I did not like it why would I want to take it home take it off my bill and offer me something else. But if you take it off my bill and give me togo that's a plus.
We had a lot of fun during the Sunday brunch
I love this place. Daily sangria specials with good food. Eric was such a friendly and attentive bartender. I will be visiting again!
Good atmosphere
The surf and turf flatbread pizza is excellent. The servers/bar staff were very sweet and helpful. Great food and a great crew. Good job guys!

I brought my daughter here for Sunday football and they gave us the entire (germ free bought) back private room.. turned on all the football games for us and let us veg out! Really amazing customer service! ERIC AND JASON ARE AWESOME!! The food and drinks are great too!!

Pretty laid back and chill atmosphere. I definitely love the Channel-side  Flatbread & they have Hookah. I wish they catered to all of their customers different taste in music, not everyone likes House Music.
Cool place to hang and grab a few.
The food was tasty. We came for drag brunch Sunday.
Great vibe
Nice place. The staff are nice
La La’s Sangria Bar is trendy and hip. 🔥🍺🥗🍹🍕🍷🔥

Great atmosphere, albeit a little overpriced.  Definitely a place to take business contacts and friends for special occasions, or whenever live talent is playing.  Extremely bougie, but that's what you get when you come to Channelside in downtown Tampa.  Looking forward to this place to offer specials on food and drinks now that the virus is over, and the owners have started recouping their losses from a very painful period.
Nice architecture, good music, beautiful women

La La’s is the perfect place if you would like to host a party. I had my 30th birthday party here and the atmosphere made it very memorable. The staff was very friendly and accommodating. The food was amazing and at a reasonable price. Also the set up was quite unique and it created just the right vibe. Even though myself and my guest party traveled from out of town just to host the party here, we all agreed that this is a place that we will definitely be returning to in the very near future. I would highly recommend this place!!
Great experience.  Or server was Isa.  She was amazing.  10/10

Best neighborhood spot in Channelside, family owned with the best atmosphere. Food is fabulous, staff of friendly and engaging but the best best part is their cigar selection :) that’s just my opinion because I’m a cigar lover.

We had excellent service, really delicious drinks, and the food was delicious as well. We ordered flatbread and wings and both were great. I'm looking forward to going back. Servers were wearing masks and it was not crowded at happy hour time on a saturday. They had outdoor space to sit.

Lala's sangria bar in Channelside fun atmosphere great food great drinks I enjoy going there most of the time I go on a Sunday door opens at 1 great drag show lots of friends owners are very friendly and caring for their customers experience you won't be like down.. MJ
This place is great. The atmosphere is awesome, entertainment is great and great food and drinks. Sunday brunch is amazing!
Bar food, yeah, awesome. One of the best spots in the area. This place has a great feel to it.
Delicious drinks!!
The only way to properly describe this experience was awesome lots of fun and laughs and awesome food
Fun atmosphere
Amazing staff and great food!
Love that place very nice crow the food is exelente and the people work there # 1
Come on Sundays for Brunch and the Best Tampa DJ!
Trendy and fun!

$90 for two pitchers of sangria (that’s 2 cups in a pitcher so 4 cups of sangria for $90)??? This place is ridiculous. They don’t even put the price of the drinks on the menu because they know their prices don’t make sense and people will immediately leave if they know the prices beforehand. I seriously want to know how the calculate their prices?
I’m here on business but stopped in and received great service. Did not try the sangria but had an amazing margarita.
Way over price

I live by this place and have gotten sangria before. It’s alright, I guess. But they have treated the entire pandemic like a joke. They don’t care about your safety, make no mistake. There are crowds of people and they do nothing about it. It’s a sketchy situation. A lot of restaurants are taking preventative measures now that things are opening up. Meanwhile, this spot is just welcoming crowds. Disgusting.  Edit for the owner: it is a fact that there were crowds at your place. I have literally seen it with my own eyes. I live right next to your place.  Don’t lie because it’s on a review.
Great casual place to hangout in Channelside.

The manager was extremely rude. I can’t believe this person works in customer service. The waitress even warned our table about him and acted as if this happened all the time. They charge for ice in drinks lol. My friends and I are pretty relaxed about bad service but this was beyond. I’m honestly not worried because of the turnover rate in channel side restaurants. Because of this manager I doubt this place will be around for more than a year.  In response to the reply-  I have never in my life, nor would I ever yell or scream at any server in a public place. None of our party was rude. Your server was actually very friendly and we were friendly with her. You the manager is the problem. Also lying in your response just validates my one star review lol.
Best place to hangout and have a drink Also cute girls here.
Have fun and relax,excellent drinks.

I wanted to love this place so much, but I have unfortunately never seen such cheap and uncomfortable chairs at any restaurant before. We were seated in a high top and actually didn't even end up staying because the chairs were so uncomfortable. Would have loved to try the food/drinks.. maybe if I want to stand next time! :)
Dempsey! Thank you for a great time Cheers 🍻
Really enjoyed my sangria and am excited to come back and try the food. Menu looked great! Staff was very friendly and cool atmosphere!

Delicious food and drinks. There’s great deals on Tuesday - the donuts are to die for (not pictured). My favorite sangria was the blueberry one. My boyfriend and I got the Brie and figs flatbread and it was fantastic. Great service and 100% recommend

A good start with room for improvement. Very friendly staff as we sat in high energy environment. Menus offers some interesting tapas style options. I was a big fan of the shrimp scampi, not such a big fan of black chocolate cherry Sangria.  I found it nice to sample a sangria flight and surprised that there were more white options than red.  Future consideration should be given to offering champagne sangria as an alternative to all moscato based white options. Coming back in a few weeks for happy hour with the girls.

I really wanted to love this place, but if you have sangria in your name you expect it to be good. I have gotten better sangria at outback. Glad I went on a Tuesday when the sangria was half priced or would have been really upset.  Definitely not worth full price. The flat bread was good, but not worth going for that alone. Our waitress was very sweet.

The drinks we're just okay but small for the price and really had none of the taste that was advertised. All the drinks I tried just tasted like basic sangria even though I ordered very different flavors. Also the barstools were very uncomfortable and I had to practically stand to keep from sliding off them.
Great atmosphere, sangria and food! Must visit while in Tampa!
Amazing food.  Great bartenders.
This place was really tasty! I liked the flatbreads in particular, had the surf and turf and channelside and bit were great. Can’t wait to go back!
Sangria was in tap but very good and food us also very good, especially the ceviche and salads
(12/27/19 visit) Had the Tropical Sangria. It is white wine based. It was ok. I expected a bolder flavor. The flavor was faint. Venue is nice and customer service was good.
Chef Maika has outstanding culinary skills!!! Food & atmosphere are top notch. Will definitely go again
Matt was a great bartender!
Fantastic, what a great concept! Super friendly staff both greeted us and served us!  Sampled their sangrias...all delicious!!!  Will return for food/dinner next time!
Matt & Jessica were friendly, attentive and provided great service!

A sangria bar should serve amazing sangria. When I received my sangria I thought that they may have messed up my order. I was confused how a blueberry lemon thyme sangria could have four bits of apple in it. After tasting it, it did not taste like blueberry, lemon or thyme. Our server came over to ask us how it tasted. I questioned if it was the right drink and she said it was. I then told her I couldn't taste the flavors in which she responded maybe it's you.  Tiramisu was not great. Hard ladyfingers and bland filling to dip them in.  Three stars for the crab cakes. Probably won't be back.

I visited Lala's today for brunch with several friends. Many ordered Sangria flights to sample several flavors and we couldn't have been more disappointed. Most had little taste and every single one, regardless of flavor, had diced apples floating on top but no other fruit that you'd expect in Sangria. Even the cherry chocolate flavor had apples floating on top. I will have to say that the food tasted fantastic. Just be aware that you're getting small plates even though you're paying for full portions and the sangria is way over priced for the quality.
We were there last week ...love the food and great service . Highly recommend !!!
Very nice atmosphere. Great Sangria. Awesome service.
Loved this place! Lala’s is officially one of my favorite spots in channelside, their ambiance is perfect and the sangria sooo yummy  ... p.s they have a doggie menu!!!
What a great place with great unusual food! Great drinks. Small plates. And open late. This is definitely needed in the Channel District.

Great environment, great prices, not just for the area but for the quality of the food and level of drink. EXTREMELY affordable for anyone to go and in an dually great spot for ease of access. The Channelside flatbread is amazing. Will deff be back.
What a wonderful addition to the Channelside District! Food was fabulous. The sticky toffee dessert and flat breads are to die for! Great ambiance and people. Good times!
Best place in Tampa. Food and service are top notch. Atmosphere is unmatched.

Ehhhh not very impressed with the bar in general. The menu is VERY hard to read. They simply printed the menu off of online and placed it in a plastic sheet. Words are very small. Service was slow - bar was pretty empty and it took about 5 minutes for the waitresses to figure out a table situation for 8 people. Waitress was SUPER rude - she said "so are you going to order something from the menu or not?".  The sangria was okay but in the smallest wine glass. You can drink way better sangria at your local Bonefish Grill.  The bar owner should've had a soft opening with people who would actually critique.
Small portion sizes. Make sure to order 2-3 plates to get full! Happy hour 4-7pm w $2 off drinks!
Beautiful place for a girls night out for cocktails

This is my first time here since the grand opening. Steven and Brent were such a delight to be served by! They were very informative, friendly, and knowledgeable! The food and drinks were fantastic! The atmosphere and decor was very homey and vibrant! I had such a great time, and will be back very soon!
Great drink's the food was delicious and our server Danielle was the best THANK YOU👍👍👍👍👍
